        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 1:29PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 129 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Wytheville, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Max Meadows...
Patterson...
Fort Chiswell...
Cripple Creek...
Grahams Forge...
and Ivanhoe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
